&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type of cooperation &lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;— &lt;/span&gt;2 month contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;At Robots &amp;amp; Pencils, we’re looking for a Senior QA Engineer (Manual) to join a newly formed, R&amp;amp;P-led team working on a greenfield application. In this role, you will play a key part in ensuring the quality, reliability, and usability of a modern platform designed to support operational workflows and distributed teams across both web and native mobile applications (iOS and Android).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll collaborate closely with engineers, product managers, and designers to define testing strategies, validate new features, and ensure high-quality releases. This is an opportunity to work from the ground up on a new product, influence QA processes, and contribute to building a strong quality culture within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In February 2025, we opened our new office in Lviv, Ukraine, as part of our ongoing global growth. We’re actively expanding our Ukrainian team and inviting skilled professionals to join us on this journey. You’ll collaborate with a distributed team working on high-impact products with colleagues across North and South America and Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Create, maintain, and execute detailed manual test cases based on user stories and requirements&lt;br&gt;• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define acceptance criteria and testing strategies&lt;br&gt;• Perform functional, regression, exploratory, and usability testing for web and native mobile applications (iOS &amp;amp; Android)&lt;br&gt;• Identify, document, and track defects through to resolution&lt;br&gt;• Validate front-end and API integrations to ensure a seamless user experience across platforms&lt;br&gt;• Contribute to continuous improvement of QA processes, standards, and best practices&lt;br&gt;• Participate in agile ceremonies and provide input on quality risks and timelines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 5+ years of experience in software quality assurance (manual testing)&lt;br&gt;• Proven experience testing both web and native mobile applications (iOS and Android)&lt;br&gt;• Strong understanding of QA methodologies, tools, and best practices&lt;br&gt;• Experience testing modern web applications&lt;br&gt;• Experience working with RESTful APIs (e.g., using Postman or similar tools)&lt;br&gt;• Solid understanding of software development lifecycle (SDLC) and agile methodologies&lt;br&gt;• Strong attention to detail and analytical thinking&lt;br&gt;• Upper-Intermediate English (written and spoken)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience working on greenfield products or in fast-paced startup-like environments&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with test management and bug tracking tools (e.g., Jira, TestRail)&lt;br&gt;• Basic understanding of front-end technologies (e.g., React, browser dev tools)&lt;br&gt;• Experience testing mobile-specific features (push notifications, offline mode, device compatibility)&lt;br&gt;• Exposure to AI-assisted testing or modern QA tooling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Robots &amp;amp; Pencils?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Robots &amp;amp; Pencils, we don’t just build software – we solve meaningful business problems through creative technology. You’ll work alongside passionate engineers, designers, and strategists in a remote-friendly, collaborative environment. With our expansion into Ukraine, now is the perfect time to join our growing global team and contribute to impactful, high-quality products.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Robots &amp;amp; Pencils is an applied AI engineering firm building the next frontier of business architecture. We design and ship AI co-workers that integrate into enterprise operations and deliver measurable results for our clients. We&#39;re all in on AWS, combining deep UX capability with senior engineering talent to get AI into production fast and keep it there. We’ve earned the trust of leaders across Consumer Products and Retail, Education, Energy, Financial Services, Healthcare, and Manufacturing and more, and earned a reputation as the nimble alternative to traditional global systems integrators. Founded in 2009, with delivery centers in Canada, the United States, Eastern Europe, and Latin America, we are smaller, faster, and more senior by design. Our teams average 15+ years of experience. We move fast, sweat the details, and build things that actually ship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Strategist to lead strategy and discovery work end-to-end across complex client engagements. This role is ideal for an experienced analyst and strategist who can independently own the full arc of an engagement — from framing the problem through delivering a clear, actionable plan — while building trusted relationships with senior client stakeholders.&lt;br&gt;In this role, you will work as the lead analyst on a cross-functional team, driving discovery, shaping recommendations, and facilitating high-impact client sessions that turn ambiguity into direction. You&#39;ll collaborate closely with strategists, designers, engineers, and delivery leads, and bring the experience and judgment to navigate complexity, competing priorities, and high-stakes decisions with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Craft &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead AI and digital strategy engagements end-to-end, from opportunity discovery and problem framing through prioritization, roadmap creation, and pilot planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map customer journeys, operational workflows, and decision points to identify where automation, AI, and digital solutions create measurable business lift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and present compelling business cases that quantify value, define KPIs, and align executive and operational stakeholders on what success looks like&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce lightweight prototypes, agent demonstrations, and proof-of-concept experiences that make strategy tangible and testable for clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with client SMEs to encode institutional knowledge into AI-ready assets including prompt libraries, evaluation examples, and retrieval corpora&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define practical governance frameworks aligned to the client&#39;s risk posture covering responsible AI principles, privacy, human-in-the-loop controls, and escalation paths&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shrink feedback loops by testing ideas early with real users and operational teams, iterating based on evidence rather than assumptions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate between business and technical teams, ensuring strategy connects cleanly to delivery across design, data, engineering, and change management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring an AI-forward mindset to your daily work, using tools like Claude, Claude Code, Cursor, and Figma AI — and agentic frameworks where relevant — to move faster than traditional consulting cycles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Communication&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently lead high-impact client sessions including executive briefings, ideation workshops, and process redesign sprints that move groups from ambiguity to a shared plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusted relationships with senior client stakeholders, serving as a reliable, consultative partner throughout the engagement

